cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it presents a multichannel medium access control (MAC) protocol for wireless ad hoc networks. It also involves spectrum sensing at the physical layer and packet scheduling at the MAC layer, which are key components of networking and internet architecture. 

It could also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it deals with cognitive radio networks, which involve the secure and efficient use of wireless spectrum. 

cs.IT (Information Theory) is another likely sub-category as the paper discusses the use of multiple channels and TDMA to achieve aggressive power savings, which involves information theory concepts. 

cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also a possible sub-category as the proposed protocol involves explicit time negotiation and the coordination of multiple nodes, which are key components of control systems. 

Finally, cs.MM (Multimedia) is a less likely sub-category, but still possible as the paper discusses the protection of QoS provisioning over cognitive radio ad hoc networks, which could involve multimedia applications.
